Ekiti State governor, Dr. Kayode Fayemi, has assured towns and communities that voted the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the last governorship election they would not be sid lined in his government’s developmental agenda. The governor also promised to ensure good performance to convince Ekiti people that voting him during the July 14 governorship poll was no mistake. Fayemi spoke at the Ekiti Parapo Pavilion in Ado Ekiti while interfacing with chairmen and secretaries of town unions across the 133 towns in the state.
The governor, represented by the Deputy Governor, Chief Bisi Egbeyemi, said projects would be distributed across all towns with no political considerations.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .